translated: Örnefors, Fritz Einar Vitalis, provincial doctor, Hohultslätt, number Årjäng, born on March 16, 1905 in Viitsand, Värmland. - Studied in Karlstad until 1926, obtained a Bachelor of Medicine degree in Uppsala in 1929, and a Medical Licentiate degree in Stockholm in 1935. Assisted at Sachsska Children's Hospital in 1935, employed as a doctor at Marieberg Hospital in 1936, served as an assistant and temporary second assistant doctor at the medical department of Karlstad General Hospital from 1936-1937, filled in as an absent doctor at Moheds Sanatorium in 1938, appointed as a regular absent doctor the same year, worked as an absent doctor at S:ta Gertrud's Hospital, Sundsvall Hospital, Växjö Hospital, and Eskilstuna Hospital from 1940-1946. Became a provincial doctor in Hohultslätt district from 1946-1947, and a provincial doctor in Årjäng from 1947 onwards.
